==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: loony
<hw>loon"y</hw> <pr>(l⟦oomac⟧n"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Shortened fr. <ets>lunatic</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Crazy;
insane; lunatic; mentally unsound.</def> <mark>[Low, U.S.]</mark>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>loony</asp>, <asp>luny</asp> and
<asp>looney</asp>.]</altsp> <def>See <er>Luny</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Very foolish; very impractical; <as>as,
<ex>loony</ex> ideas</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>loony</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: loony
<hw>loony</hw> <pr>(l⟦oomac⟧n"⟦ycr⟧)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <def>someone
mentally deranged and possibly dangerous.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> crazy, looney, weirdo, psycho.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

